"```sql\nSELECT \n  ((y2012.Consumption - y2013.Consumption) / y2012.Consumption) AS ConsumptionDecreaseRate\nFROM \n  transactions_1k t\nJOIN \n  yearmonth y2012 ON t.CustomerID = y2012.CustomerID AND y2012.Date LIKE '2012%'\nJOIN \n  yearmonth y2013 ON t.CustomerID = y2013.CustomerID AND y2013.Date LIKE '2013%'\nWHERE \n  t.Amount = 634.8 AND t.Date = '2012-08-25';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the consumption decrease rate for the customer who made a transaction of 634.8 on 2012-08-25. It joins the `transactions_1k` table with the `yearmonth` table for both 2012 and 2013 to find the consumption for each year and then calculates the decrease rate."